-- Cotton Futures in New York, China Advance to Records on Increased Demand
-- B y   M a t t h e w   O a k l e y
-- 2010-11-03T01:07:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-03/cotton-futures-in-new-york-china-advance-to-records-on-increased-demand.html
Cotton futures traded in New York and
Zhengzhou advanced to records.  Cotton for December delivery on ICE Futures U.S. gained for
a fourth day, adding as much as 1.3 percent to $1.3598 a pound,
and traded at $1.3564 at 9:05 a.m. in Singapore.  Cotton for July delivery on the Zhengzhou Commodity
Exchange gained as much as 2.5 percent to 29,485 yuan ($4,415) a
metric ton.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Matthew Oakley at 
 moakley@bloomberg.net  